<P>22. However, the trial judge found that the respondent established that she had been induced into the Contract by fraudulent misrepresentation entitling her to rescission, and $4,040.44 in damages for legal advice regarding the collapsed sale.
<P1>RFJ paras. 221&ndash;225</P1></P>
<P>23. The judge found that the Vendor made a false misrepresentation when she gave as the reason for selling the Property her granddaughter's change of schools but concealed that the school had asked her to leave following Mr. Huang's death.
