<P>24. Following a <EM>voir dire</EM>, the trial judge refused to permit Patrick Fogarty, a former Vancouver police member and chief of Combined Forces Special Enforcement Unit to testify about the Big Circle gang's origin in Chairman Mao's Red Army, and Raymond Huang's top ranking in national priority on the &ldquo;Sleipnir matrix&rdquo;.
<P1>T, p.675 ll. 6&ndash;12, p. 686, l 27 to p. 687, l. 21&ndash;69, p. 683, ll. 25&ndash;34, p. 682. ll. 22&ndash;47</P1></P>
<P>25. Mr. Fogarty testified on the <EM>voire dire</EM> that Mr. Huang was the number one priority threat in the country in 2007.
<P1>T, p. 690, ll. 9&ndash;12</P1></P>
<P>26. The trial took 14 days including proceedings by video and Chinese&mdash;English interpreters.</P></BLOCK3>
