<P1>T, p. 491, ll. 31&ndash;33, 492, ll. 6&ndash;11, p. 508, ll. 21&ndash;23, p. 509, l. 17 to p. 510 l. 1, p. 540, ll. 6&ndash;20, p. 542, II. 22&ndash;35, p. 550, II. 31&ndash;35</P1></P>
<P>57. The killing of Mr. Huang was never mentioned. Winnie's realtors did not tell Mrs. Shao that after Mr. Huang's death, West Point Grey Academy asked Winnie's daughter to leave the school.
