<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="I">AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Cherie Lam, legal assistant, c/o #100-8210 Granville Avenue, Richmond, British Columbia, V6Y 1P3, SOLEMNLY AFFIRM AND SAY THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am legal assistant to Mr. Wallace M. Wong, counsel for the Respondent, and as such, have personal knowledge of the facts to which I depose except where stated to be on information and belief, in which case I believe the statements to be true.</P>
<P>2. I am informed by Mr. Wong that the Appellant, Mei Zhen Wang, testified at the trial of this matter that she returned to China permanently in 2007. I am informed by Mr. Wong that China is a non-reciprocating jurisdiction.</P>
<P>3. I am informed by Mr. Wong that examination for discovery of the Appellant was conducted in Macao, China, because she was unwilling or unable to come to Vancouver, B.C. to be examined.</P>
<P>4. I am further informed that the Appellant did not attend the trial in person. Instead, she appeared by video conference because she was unwilling or unable to come to Vancouver, B.C.</P>
<P>5. I am informed by Mr. Wong that the Appellant lives in China, a nonreciprocating jurisdiction, that the Respondent has demanded that the Appellant pay the costs awarded to the Respondent in the court below, that the Appellant has refused to pay such costs, and that the appellant has no exigible assets in British Columbia.</P>
<P>6. I am informed by Mr. Wong that the Bill of Costs for the appeal of this matter, a copy of which is attached to this Affidavit as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;,</BOLD> is a reasonable estimate of the taxable costs and disbursements to which the Respondent will be entitled if she is successful on this appeal. I believe <BOLD><UNDER>$10,740.00</UNDER></BOLD> is a reasonable estimate of the amount that will be assessed against the Appellant as costs if the Respondent is successful on this appeal.</P>
<P>7. The Appellant was ordered to pay costs to be assessed as ordinary costs at scale B for 13 days and reasonable disbursements. I am informed by Mr. Wong that he believes that the Bill of Costs, a copy of which is attached to this Affidavit as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;,</BOLD> is a reasonable estimate of the amount of the ordinary costs and disbursements that will be assessed against the Appellant in the Court below. I believe that <BOLD><UNDER>$124,638.13</UNDER></BOLD> is a reasonable estimate of the amount that will be assessed against the Appellant as costs in the Court below.</P>
<P>8. I am informed by Mr. Wong that he believes that if the appeal is unsuccessful, the Respondent will not be able to collect its costs of the appeal or in the Court below.</P>
