<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT #1 OF PALMINA BRIGGS</TI>
<P>I, PALMINA BRIGGS, Legal Assistant, of 1600 - 1095 West Pender Street, Vancouver, British Columbia, HEREBY AFFIRM THAT:</P>
<P>1. I am a legal assistant at the law firm MacKenzie Fujisawa LLP, counsel for the appellant Mei Zhen Wang in this matter and, as such, have personal knowledge of the matters deposed to herein, except where stated to be on information and belief and where so stated I verily believe to be true.</P>
<P>2. The respondent's Notice of Motion was served on counsel for the appellant on January 16, 2019. I have thoroughly reviewed our file, including all emails and correspondence, and I am advised by Quang T. Duong, counsel for the appellant at trial that contrary to the facts alleged in paragraph 5 of Cherie Lam's affidavit, at no time prior to service of this motion has there been a demand for trial costs made by the respondent or her counsel. Prior to January 16, 2019 the appellant had not received a bill of trial costs from the respondent.</P>
<P>3. The estimated bill of costs for the trial, attached as Exhibit &lsquo;B&rsquo; to Ms. Cherie Lam's Affidavit, has not been assessed in the trial court. The respondent has not made an application nor taken any steps to assess the trial costs.</P>
<P>4. The appellant has already incurred nearly all of the costs required to prepare the case for appeal, including costs of preparing the appeal books, transcripts and factum. All that remains to be expended are the costs in relation to the hearing of the appeal, now scheduled for March 7, 2019.</P>
<P>5. The appellant, Mrs. Wang, is aged 84 and resides in China. I am advised by Mr. Duong that due to health reasons, Mrs. Wang could not travel to Vancouver for examinations for discovery or for trial. I am further advised by Mr. Duong that Mrs. Wang is illiterate and does not speak English.</P>
<P>6. I am further advised by Mr. Duong that, as of the date of swearing of this affidavit, he has not been able to communicate with the appellant with respect to her ability to pay costs. The process of communicating with the appellant requires translations by the appellant's daughter or granddaughter. Mr. Duong advises me that he is concerned about his ability to make arrangements with the appellant for the posting of security before the hearing of the appeal on March 7, 2019.</P>
<P>7. The respondent's bill of costs in respect of the appeal reflects, for some tariff items, the maximum allowable under the tariff for a full day appeal. Attached and marked as <BOLD>Exhibit &lsquo;A&rsquo;</BOLD> is a draft bill of costs reflecting tariff items in the mid-range, for a half-day appeal.</P>
